<title>RUSSIA: Yeltsin orders public sector wages paid by October.</title>
<headline>Yeltsin orders public sector wages paid by October.</headline>
<dateline>MOSCOW 1997-07-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>Russian President Boris Yeltsin has ordered the government to pay wage arrears to the army within two months and to other public sector workers such as teachers within three months, the Kremlin said on Wednesday.</p>
<p>Yeltsin told Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin to ensure the payments were made, a presidential press spokesman told Reuters. No figure for the arrears was available but they are estimated to run to billions of dollars.</p>
